United Co. Rusal, Razgulay, Evraz Group: Russian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-05-18T20:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/united-co-rusal-razgulay-evraz-group-russian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be active
in Russian trading in Moscow. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are from the previous close of trading.  Russia’s 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  added 1.1 percent to 1,627.03
yesterday. The dollar-denominated RTS Index gained 1.1 percent
to 1,849.60.  United Co. Rusal (486 HK): The world’s largest maker of
aluminum will challenge a Ukrainian court’s ruling that
ownership of a smelter should be returned to the state,
according to an e-mailed statement from the company. Rusal added
3.8 percent to HK$ 11.08.  Razgulay Group (GRAZ RX): Russian farmers planted 16.4
million hectares (40.5 million acres) with spring grains as of
today, or 14 percent more than a year earlier, the country’s
 Agriculture Ministry  said in an e-mailed statement. Razgulay, a
Russian grain and sugar producer, dropped 2.2 percent to 60.50
rubles.  Evraz Group SA (EVR LI):  Evraz Group SA (EVR)  will probably
decide on the future of its holding in OAO Raspadskaya, once the
largest Russian producer of coal for steelmaking, after August,
according to Evraz’s Vice President on Communications Oleg
Kuzmin. Russia’s second-largest steelmaker added 2.4 percent to
$31.91 in  London .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
